<subSubSection id="7BFFEAD3FFBBA74C0CE0F9F5FDBCA691" lastPageId="118" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="335AB958FFBBA74E0CE0F9F5FD6AA0D2" blockId="116.[151,1436,1659,2034]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="0191654AFFBBA74E0CE0F9F5FEBEA0FB" bold="true" box="[151,271,1659,1685]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species was redescribed and fully illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="5774C4A9FFBBA74E0FEBF9F2FBECA0F8" author="Rohacek, J." box="[924,1117,1659,1686]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref102787" refString="Rohacek, J. (1982) Revision of the subgenus Leptocera (s. str.) of Europe (Diptera, Sphaeroceridae). Entomologische Abhandlungen, Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 46, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="1982">Roháček (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. Body length 
<quantity id="F41D14BDFFBBA74E0972F9F2FA29A0F8" box="[1285,1432,1660,1686]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.4 mm</quantity>
. External characters as in species group diagnosis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="335AB958FFBBA74E0CB0F947FC75A19C" blockId="116.[151,1436,1659,2034]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="ABDEA5DDFFBBA74E0DEAF947FDE3A08D" box="[413,594,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 273–278" captionStartId="117.[151,269,1841,1865]" captionTargetBox="[233,1348,227,1815]" captionTargetId="figure-80@117.[229,1351,194,1817]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURES 273–278. Leptocera nigra (273–275: Spain, 276–278: Venezuela). Male terminalia (phallus and postgonites omitted): (273) lateral; (274) posterior; (275) sternite 5. Female terminalia: (276) dorsal; (277) spermathecae; (278) sternites 7 and 8. ass—anterior section of surstylus, ce—cercus, cp—ventral process of cercus, ep—epandrium, fm—field of dense microtrichia, ha—hypandrial apodeme, pa—phallapodeme, pss—posterior section of surstylus, S—sternite, se—subepandrial sclerite, T—tergite (female tergite 8 divided into two halves)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311968/files/figure.png" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Figs. 273–275</figureCitation>
): Sternite 5 with lobes on each side of posteromedial emargination spinulose, simple (i.e., without medial digitiform process). Anterior section of surstylus with extremely reduced anterior process (omitted in 
<bibRefCitation id="5774C4A9FFBBA74E0E20F898FCBFA15E" author="Rohacek, J." box="[599,782,1814,1840]" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref102787" refString="Rohacek, J. (1982) Revision of the subgenus Leptocera (s. str.) of Europe (Diptera, Sphaeroceridae). Entomologische Abhandlungen, Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 46, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="1982">Roháček, 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 
